lyrics:
Verse 1)
In the city of shadows where the neon lights gleam,
Lost souls chasing dreams, in a world so extreme.
Guitar strings scream, as the night takes hold,
Concrete jungle stories, in the alleys untold.

(Pre-Chorus)
We're dancing on the edge, where the fire burns bright,
In the heart of the chaos, we find our own light.
Through the thunder and rain, we stand tall,
Rock 'n' roll rebels, breaking down the wall.

(Chorus)
This is the anthem of the restless,
In the rhythm of rebellion, we confess.
Through the highs and the lows,
In the language of rock, our story unfolds.
